{
  "texts": [
    "The second model, SymP (Reweighting), 29 builds upon the original SymP framework by integrating reweighting techniques to more effectively address challenges related to missing labels and data imbalance.",
    "By adjusting the weight of symptoms based on their predicted relevance and presence, this enhanced version of SymP demonstrates a sophisticated approach to navigating the intricacies of mental health symptom identification.",
    "Details of experiment settings can be found in Appendix A.",
    "Although LLMs like GPT variants and BERT models train differently, both have become valuable tools in understanding natural language.",
    "LLMs typically learn through unsupervised learning, which means they get better at predicting text by reading lots of it."
  ]
}